'''Waldemar Anton''' ({{IPA|de|ˈvaldemaːʁ ˈantɔn|-|}}; born 20 July 1996) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]].

==Club career==
===Hannover 96 (2015–2020)===
Anton played eleven matches for [[Hannover 96 II]] and scored one goal.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Waldemar Anton » Club matches|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe263614/waldemar-anton/club-matches/|access-date=11 November 2021|website=WorldFootball.net}}</ref> Since [[Hannover 96]] were in [[relegation]], Anton and [[Mike-Steven Bähre]] were signed to professional contracts to help the club.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Bundesliga: Hannover verlängert mit Retter Frontzeck|language=de|work=FAZ.NET|url=https://www.faz.net/aktuell/sport/fussball/bundesliga/bundesliga-hannover-96-verlaengert-vertrag-mit-frontzeck-13617348.html|access-date=2021-11-11|issn=0174-4909}}</ref>

[[File:Anton, Waldemar H96 16-17 WP.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Anton with [[Hannover 96]] in 2016]]
During the 2015–16 season, Anton made two appearances for [[Hannover 96]],<ref name="Waldemar Anton » Club matches">{{cite web|title=Waldemar Anton » Club matches|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe263614/waldemar-anton/club-matches/|website=WorldFootball.net|access-date=31 March 2016}}</ref> playing in a 2–1 win against [[VfB Stuttgart]] on 27 February 2016<ref>{{cite news|title=Schulz und Kiyotake beatmen Hannover|url=https://www.kicker.de/stuttgart-gegen-hannover-2016-bundesliga-2855134/analyse|access-date=31 March 2016|publisher=kicker|date=27 February 2016|language=de}}</ref> and a 1–0 loss against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on 19 March 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ben-Hatira entscheidet den Abstiegskrimi|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-hannover-2016-bundesliga-2855417/analyse|access-date=31 March 2016|publisher=kicker|date=19 March 2016|language=German}}</ref> His first Bundesliga goal was against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] on 15 April 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Anton und Sobiech brechen den Heimfluch|url=https://www.kicker.de/hannover-gegen-mgladbach-2016-bundesliga-2855443/analyse|access-date=15 April 2016|publisher=kicker|date=15 April 2016|language=German}}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart (2020–2024)===
On 28 July 2020, Anton transferred to [[VfB Stuttgart]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/vfb_macht_anton_transfer_perfekt_jackson_martinez_kein_thema-780627/artikel |title=VfB macht Anton-Transfer perfekt – Jackson Martinez kein Thema |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |publisher=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]] |date=28 July 2020 |access-date=28 July 2020 |language=de}}</ref> On 5 November 2021, he extended his contract until 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-11-05|title=Waldemar Anton verlängert bis 2025|url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/profis/2122/waldemar-anton-verlaengert-bis-2025/|access-date=2021-11-05|website=VfB Stuttgart|language=de}}</ref>

[[File:Waldemar anton.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Anton with [[VfB Stuttgart]] in 2022]]
Anton became the team captain of VfB Stuttgart in August 2023 and extended his contract until 2027 on 14 January 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-01-14|title=Anton extends contract through to 2027|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/waldemar-anton-2027/|access-date=2024-01-14|website=VfB Stuttgart}}</ref> On 4 May 2024, the final matchday of the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] season, Anton would help his side win 3–1 over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], thus finishing Bundesliga runner-up behind champions [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=sportschau.de |title=FC Bayern vergeigt Generalprobe: Stuttgart gewinnt mal wieder gegen München |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/bundesliga/vfb-gewinnt-mal-wieder-gegen-fc-bayern,bundesliga-spielbericht-stuttgart-bayern-muenchen-100.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=sportschau.de |language=de}}</ref>

===Borussia Dortmund (since 2024)===
On 8 July 2024, Anton joined fellow Bundesliga club [[Borussia Dortmund]], signing a four-year contract,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/en/news/news-overview/news.html/waldemar-anton-signs-until-2028.html |title=Waldemar Anton signs until 2028 |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |date=8 July 2024 |access-date=8 July 2024 }}</ref> for a reported transfer fee of €22.5m, as a replacement for [[Mats Hummels]], who left the club in the same summer.<ref>{{cite web |last=Fitzpatrick |first=Peter |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/borussia-dortmund-complete-signing-of-stuttgart-defender-39734690 |title=Borussia Dortmund complete signing of Stuttgart defender |publisher=OneFootball |date=8 July 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-08 |title=Hummels-Nachfolger da: BVB macht Verpflichtung von Waldemar Anton perfekt |url=https://www.wa.de/sport/borussia-dortmund/hummels-nachfolger-bvb-dortmund-transfer-waldemar-anton-2028-zr-93175766.html |access-date=2026-04-11 |website=www.wa.de |language=de}}</ref> The transfer has caused major controversies among Stuttgart supporters, since Anton declared his loyalty towards the club four months earlier.<ref>{{Cite news |title="Vor allem meiner Familie wegen": BVB-Transfer Waldemar Anton hofft auf abnehmende Hassnachrichten aus Stuttgart {{!}} SPOX |url=https://www.spox.com/fussball/listen/vor-allem-der-familie-wegen-bvb-transfer-waldemar-anton-hofft-auf-abnehmende-hassnachrichten-aus-stuttgart/6827444 |access-date=2026-04-06 |language=de}}</ref>

