On 17 August 2024, Anton made his Dortmund debut in the first round of the [[2024–25 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] against [[1. FC Phönix Lübeck|Phönix Lübeck]], scoring three minutes into the match, and thus his first goal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=4:1 – BVB überspringt vor Rekordkulisse die Hürde Lübeck |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2024/8/17/41-BVB-ueberspringt-vor-Rekordkulisse-die-Huerde-Luebeck.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> On 18 September, he'd celebrate his [[UEFA club competitions|European]] debut coming on as a substitute in a 3–0 away victory over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]], on the first matchday of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kicker.de |date=18 September 2024 |title=Club Brügge gegen Dortmund 2024 Champions League |url=https://www.kicker.de/club-bruegge-gegen-dortmund-2024-champions-league-4962784/ticker |url-status=live |access-date=6 April 2026 |website=Kicker}}</ref> On 1 October, he'd feature in the starting line-up in the Champions League for the first time, in a 7–1 home win over [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic Glasgow]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Borussia Dortmund feiert 7:1-Sternstunde gegen Celtic |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2024/10/1/Borussia-Dortmund-feiert-71-Sternstunde-gegen-Celtic.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> On 8 February 2025, Anton scored an [[own goal]] for his former club VfB Stuttgart in a 2–1 loss.<ref>{{Cite web |title=VfB Stuttgart ruin Niko Kovač's Borussia Dortmund debut |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-vfb-stuttgart-match-report-highlights-matchday-21-30858 |access-date=2025-03-01 |website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref> On 12 April, he scored his first [[2024–25 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] goal for Dortmund away in [[FC Bayern Munich|Munich]], to tie the game 2–2 and secure a point for his team.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kicker.de |title=Bayern gegen Dortmund 2025 Bundesliga |url=https://www.kicker.de/bayern-gegen-dortmund-2025-bundesliga-4937039/ticker |url-status=live |access-date=6 April 2026 |website=Kicker}}</ref> Three days later, he'd play full 90 minutes in a 3–1 home victory over [[FC Barcelona]], in the quarter-final of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], though his side was eliminated.<ref>{{Cite web |title=BVB schlägt Barcelona 3:1 – Raus mit dröhnendem Applaus! |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2025/4/15/BVB-schlaegt-Barcelona-31-Raus-mit-droehnendem-Applaus.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> On 26 April, he'd score the winning goal for Dortmund in the sixth minute of extra time in a 3–2 away victory over [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|Hoffenheim]], climbing up to the sixth place of the league table, making a crucial step towards [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] qualification for the following season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=3:2 – Anton schießt BVB in letzter Sekunde zum Sieg in Sinsheim |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2025/4/26/32-Anton-schiesst-BVB-in-letzter-Sekunde-zum-Sieg-in-Sinsheim.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> On the last matchday, he would help his team win 3–0 against [[Holstein Kiel|Kiel]] and qualify for the Champions League.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kicker.de |title=Bundesliga Tabelle 34. Spieltag |url=https://www.kicker.de/bundesliga/tabelle |url-status=live |access-date=6 April 2026 |website=Kicker}}</ref>

In the first matchday of the following [[2025–26 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] season, he'd score a goal in a 3–3 draw over [[FC St. Pauli|St. Pauli]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=3:3 beim FC St. Pauli – BVB verspielt nach Manes Platzverweis 3:1-Führung |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2025/8/23/33-beim-FC-St-Pauli-BVB-verspielt-nach-Manes-Platzverweis-31-Fuehrung.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> On 5 November 2025, he'd score Dortmund's only goal in a 1–4 away loss to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], marking Dortmund's first defeat of the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=1:4 – Borussia kassiert in Manchester erste Champions-League-Niederlage der Saison |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/de/aktuelles/news/news.html/2025/11/5/14-Borussia-kassiert-in-Manchester-erste-Champions-League-Niederlage-der-Saison.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> On 4 April 2026, Dortmund would win 2–0 against [[VfB Stuttgart]] away, marking Anton's first victory with Dortmund over his ex-club after three winless matches in a row.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hochrainer |first=Sebastian |title=Adeyemi und Brandt veredeln starke BVB-Defensive in Stuttgart |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/bundesliga/adeyemi-und-brandt-veredeln-starke-bvb-defensive-in-stuttgart,spielbericht-vfb-stuttgart-borussia-dortmund-110.html |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=sportschau.de |language=de}}</ref> With Dortmund, he'd finish [[Bundesliga]] runner-up, thus qualifying for the [[2026–27 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] and the [[2026 Franz Beckenbauer Supercup|Supercup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bundesliga 2025/26 - Tabelle {{!}} 34. Spieltag |url=https://www.kicker.de/bundesliga/tabelle |access-date=2026-05-24 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayern im Franz-Beckenbauer-Supercup 2026 gegen den BVB |url=https://www.kicker.de/bayern-im-franz-beckenbauer-supercup-2026-gegen-den-bvb-1213199/artikel |access-date=2026-05-24 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref>

==International career==
Anton was eligible to play for [[Germany national football team|Germany]], [[Russia national football team|Russia]] and [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]]. He was a youth international for Germany.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Waldemar Anton Personenprofil|url=https://www.dfb.de/profil/263614|access-date=2021-11-11|website=DFB Datencenter|language=de}}</ref> He won the [[UEFA European Under-21 Championship|UEFA Under-21 Championship]] in [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2017]] and was a runner-up in [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2019]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Spain beat Germany to win U21 Euros|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48812993|access-date=2021-11-11}}</ref>

In March 2024, he was called up for the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]] ahead of the friendly matches against [[France national football team|France]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-mit-sechs-neulingen-und-sechs-rueckkehrern-259584/|title=Start ins EM-Jahr mit sechs Neulingen und sechs Rückkehrern|date=14 March 2024|publisher=[[German Football Association]] |access-date=14 March 2024|language=de }}</ref> He made his debut on 23 March 2024 in a 2–0 away win over France.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Germany 2-0 France (23 Mar, 2024) Final Score - ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/690850/germany-france |access-date=2025-03-01 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

Anton was named in Germany's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]], making his tournament debut in the round of 16 against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]], a 2–0 win in [[Dortmund]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Germany 2-0 Denmark (Jun 29, 2024) Game Analysis - ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/703932 |access-date=2026-05-24 |website=www.espn.com}}</ref> In the quarter-final against Spain, he'd play the full extra time, a 2–1 loss.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Spain 2-1 Germany (Jul 5, 2024) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/703939/germany-spain |access-date=2026-05-24 |website=www.espn.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://olympics.com/en/news/uefa-euro-2024-all-squads-and-players-full-list|title=UEFA Euro 2024: All squads and players full list|date=7 June 2024|access-date=7 June 2024|website=Olympics.com}}</ref> After the [[UEFA European Championship|Euros]], he featured in Germany's [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League]] campaign, reaching the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|finals]] and finishing fourth place.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Julian Nagelsmann names Germany squad for UEFA Nations League finals |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/julian-nagelsmann-germany-squad-uefa-nations-league-finals-32345 |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website |language=en}}</ref> Later, he successfully qualified with Germany for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], featuring in four out of their six [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifying matches]] and would be called up for the final tournament squad.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=European Qualifiers Germany squad |url=https://de.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/teams/47--germany/squad/ |url-status=live |access-date=6 April 2026 |website=UEFA.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-21 |title=So viel 96 steckt im WM-Kader: Waldemar Anton und Maximilian Beier fahren zur Weltmeisterschaft |url=https://www.hannover96.de/newscenter/news/details/37002-so-viel-96-steckt-im-wm-kader-waldemar-anton-und-maximilian-beier-fahren-zur-weltmeisterschaft.html |access-date=2026-05-22 |website=www.hannover96.de |language=de}}</ref>

==Personal life==
A ''[[Spätaussiedler]]'', Anton was born in the [[Ex-Soviet countries|ex-Soviet]] region of [[Olmaliq]], [[Uzbekistan]], to [[Russia Germans|Russia-German]] parents and moved to [[Germany]] at the age of two.<ref name="bild2018">{{cite news |title={{lang|de|"Ich brauche keine Ausstiegsklausel"|nocat=yes}} |trans-title=“I do not need a walkaway clause” |url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/hannover-96/anton-interview-keine-ausstiegsklausel-54511484.bild.html |work=[[Bild]] |language=German |date=17 January 2018 |access-date=8 July 2024 |quote=Ich bin mit meinen Eltern nach Deutschland gekommen, als ich zwei war. Da hieß ich wirklich noch Wladimir. Im deutschen Pass stand dann aber gleich Waldemar. |trans-quote=I came to Germany with my parents when I was two. My real name then was still Vladimir. But my German passport then said Waldemar.}}</ref> His father is from [[Ekaterinburg]], [[Russia]], and his mother is [[Volga Germans|Volga German]].<ref name="sports.ru2016">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports.ru/tribuna/blogs/uzbekfootball/957428.html |title={{lang|de|"Wer ist Anton Waldemar"?|nocat=yes}} {{lang|ru|Потенциальная звезда Узбекистана из Германии|nocat=yes}} |trans-title=“Who is Waldemar Anton?” Uzbekistan's potential star from Germany |last={{lang|ru|Раимов}} |first={{lang|ru|Евдоким}} |website=Sports.ru |language=ru |date=31 May 2016 |access-date=8 July 2024}}</ref> When in Germany, his parents legally changed his birth name ''[[Vladimir]]'' to its German equivalent ''[[Waldemar]]'' due to assimilation reasons.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redaktion |first=MOPO |last2=Simon |first2=imago/Sven |last3=imago1046600039h-scaled |date=2024-06-22 |title=„Mein Geburtsname ist Wladimir“: Dieser DFB-Star ersetzt Hummels beim BVB |url=https://www.mopo.de/sport/em2024/mein-geburtsname-ist-wladimir-dfb-star-anton-ersetzt-hummels-beim-bvb/ |access-date=2026-04-06 |website=MOPO |language=de}}</ref> He is [[Christianity|Christian]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kosian |first=Markus |date=2024-07-10 |title=Waldemar Anton: "Der Glaube hilft mir in Momenten, in denen ich Sorgen oder Probleme habe" |url=https://promisglauben.de/waldemar-anton-der-glaube-hilft-mir-in-momenten-in-denen-ich-sorgen-oder-probleme-habe/ |access-date=2026-04-09 |website=PromisGlauben |language=de}}</ref>

